# 🛡️ APT Lifecycle Simulation – Hybrid Windows Environment

This assessment simulated an advanced persistent threat (APT) lifecycle within a hybrid Windows environment, validating the detection and response capabilities of the Microsoft 365 Defender stack.

---

## 🔴 Red Team: Attack Lifecycle Matrix

| Phase             | Methodology                        | Tools & CVEs          | Impact                                                                 |
|-------------------|------------------------------------|-----------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Initial Access    | Kerberoasting / AS-REP Roasting    | GetUserSPNs.py        | Compromised **jon.snow** account via offline hash cracking.             |
| Lateral Movement  | SMB Relay via SOCKS Proxy          | ntlmrelayx.py         | Full Administrative Access to **CASTELBLACK** by relaying NTLM sessions.|
| Privilege Esc.    | sAMAccountName Spoofing            | CVE-2021-42278        | Exploited KDC validation flaws to impersonate Domain Controller.        |
| Domain Dominance  | DCSync / NTDS Dumping              | secretsdump.py        | Extracted all domain NTLM hashes, including **Administrator** & **krbtgt**. |
| App Exploitation  | MSSQL xp_cmdshell RCE              | mssqlclient.py        | OS-level code execution on DB tier as **sql_svc** account.              |
| Persistence       | Kerberos Golden Ticket             | ticketer.py           | Forged long-term TGT for permanent domain resource access.              |

---

## 🔵 Blue Team: Detection & XDR Validation

- **Identity Detections (MDI):** Alerted on *Suspected sAMAccountName spoofing* and *Possible Kerberoasting LDAP reconnaissance*.  
- **Endpoint Detections (EDR):** Flagged *Indication of local security authority secrets theft* during secretsdump on CASTELBLACK.  
- **Incident Correlation:** Unified alert story linking CVE-2021-42278 (account renaming) with CVE-2021-42287 (suspicious TGS requests).  

---

## ⚙️ Security Controls & Recommendations

| Security Control       | Recommendation                                                   | Objective                                                                 |
|------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Enforce SMB Signing    | Enable **"Digitally sign communications (always)"** via GPO.    | Prevents NTLM relay attacks used for lateral movement.                    |
| Rotate KRBTGT Key      | Perform double-reset of **krbtgt** account password.            | Invalidates all forged Golden Tickets.                                    |
| Tiered Admin Model     | Restrict Domain Admin logins to **Tier 0 (DCs)** only.          | Prevents credential harvesting from lower-security workstations.          |
| Zero Quota Policy      | Set **ms-DS-MachineAccountQuota = 0**.                          | Stops standard users from creating machine accounts for spoofing attacks. |

